From: Paul <paul@thingino.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 03:50:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] fix timed fire buffer overflow in thingino-button

The timed_fires[].count field is incremented on every key press when
adding TIMED_FIRE entries, but never reset. On key release, entries are
deactivated (active = 0) but count stays at its peak value. After 100+
presses on the same key, writes go past entries[MAX_CONFIGS] and
corrupt adjacent memory including the count field itself, causing the
check loop to read garbage entry->config pointers, resulting in a
SIGSEGV.

Fix:
1. Add bounds check on TIMED_FIRE entry creation to cap at MAX_CONFIGS.
2. Reset count to 0 on key release after deactivating all entries, since
   all entries for that key are inactive at that point and the next press
   will start fresh from index 0.

Signed-off-by: Paul <paul@thingino.com>

--- a/thingino-button.c
+++ b/thingino-button.c
@@ -340,6 +340,9 @@
 							gettimeofday(&press_times[ev.code], NULL);
 							// log_message("Press time recorded for key code %d\n", ev.code);
 						} else if (ev.code == config->key_code && strcmp(config->action, ACTION_TIMED_FIRE) == 0) {
+							if (timed_fires[ev.code].count >= MAX_CONFIGS) {
+								continue;
+							}
 							TimedFireEntry entry = {0};
 							gettimeofday(&entry.press_time, NULL);
 							entry.config = config;
@@ -384,6 +387,7 @@
 					for (int i = 0; i < timed_fires[ev.code].count; i++) {
 						timed_fires[ev.code].entries[i].active = 0;
 					}
+					timed_fires[ev.code].count = 0;
 				}
 			}
 		} else if (n == -1 && errno != EAGAIN) {
